article.headline: Belmont 98, Kennesaw State 52
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- J.J. Mann scored 17 points and Brandon Baker added 16 as Belmont routed Kennesaw State 98-52 on Thursday night in the Atlantic Sun Conference opener for both teams. The Bruins (4-2) are undefeated in their league home openers and have won four straight games. Belmont held the Owls (2-4) scoreless for the first 4:20 en route to an 11-0 lead. The Bruins were 15 of 39 from beyond the arc, hitting 10 3-pointers in the first half. Belmont also had 30 assists -- one shy of the program record set at Gardner-Webb on Jan. 9, 2003. The Bruins led 48-31 at halftime and stretched the lead to 62-36 four minutes into the second half. Belmont outshot Kennesaw State from the field 54.4 percent (37 of 68) to 40 percent (20 of 50) and had a 43-25 rebounding advantage with just four turnovers. Markeith Cummings led the Owls with 21 points.
